=3D"markdown" dir=3D"ltr"><span class=3D"md svelte-ftv0x7"><h2>ABOUT</h2>
<p>With the plethora of large language models (LLMs) and chatbots being rel=
eased week upon week, often with grandiose claims of their performance, it =
can be hard to filter out the genuine progress that is being made by the op=
en-source community and which model is the current state of the art.</p>
<p>=F0=9F=A4=97 Submit a model for automated evaluation on the =F0=9F=A4=97=
 GPU cluster on the "Submit" page!
The leaderboard's backend runs the great <a href=3D"https://github.com/Eleu=
therAI/lm-evaluation-harness" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer"=
>Eleuther AI Language Model Evaluation Harness</a> - read more details belo=
w!</p>
<h3>Tasks</h3>
<p>=F0=9F=93=88 We evaluate models on 6 key benchmarks using the <a href=3D=
"https://github.com/EleutherAI/lm-evaluation-harness" target=3D"_blank" rel=
=3D"noopener noreferrer">  Eleuther AI Language Model Evaluation Harness </=
a>, a unified framework to test generative language models on a large numbe=
r of different evaluation tasks.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://arxiv.org/abs/1803.05457" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"n=
oopener noreferrer">  AI2 Reasoning Challenge </a> (25-shot) - a set of gra=
de-school science questions.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://arxiv.org/abs/1905.07830" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"n=
oopener noreferrer">  HellaSwag </a> (10-shot) - a test of commonsense infe=
rence, which is easy for humans (~95%) but challenging for SOTA models.</li=
>
<li><a href=3D"https://arxiv.org/abs/2009.03300" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"n=
oopener noreferrer">  MMLU </a>  (5-shot) - a test to measure a text model'=
s multitask accuracy. The test covers 57 tasks including elementary mathema=
tics, US history, computer science, law, and more.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://arxiv.org/abs/2109.07958" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"n=
oopener noreferrer">  TruthfulQA </a> (0-shot) - a test to measure a model'=
s propensity to reproduce falsehoods commonly found online. Note: TruthfulQ=
A is technically a 6-shot task in the Harness because each example is prepe=
nded with 6 Q/A pairs, even in the 0-shot setting.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://arxiv.org/abs/1907.10641" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"n=
oopener noreferrer">  Winogrande </a> (5-shot) - an adversarial and difficu=
lt Winograd benchmark at scale, for commonsense reasoning.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://arxiv.org/abs/2110.14168" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"n=
oopener noreferrer">  GSM8k </a> (5-shot) - diverse grade school math word =
problems to measure a model's ability to solve multi-step mathematical reas=
oning problems.</li>
</ul>
<p>For all these evaluations, a higher score is a better score.
We chose these benchmarks as they test a variety of reasoning and general k=
nowledge across a wide variety of fields in 0-shot and few-shot settings.</=
p>
<h3>Results</h3>
<p>You can find:</p>
<ul>
<li>detailed numerical results in the <code>results</code> Hugging Face dat=
aset: <a href=3D"https://huggingface.co/datasets/open-llm-leaderboard/resul=
ts" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">https://huggingface.co/da=
tasets/open-llm-leaderboard/results</a></li>
<li>details on the input/outputs for the models in the <code>details</code>=
 of each model, that you can access by clicking the =F0=9F=93=84 emoji afte=
r the model name</li>
<li>community queries and running status in the <code>requests</code> Huggi=
ng Face dataset: <a href=3D"https://huggingface.co/datasets/open-llm-leader=
board/requests" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">https://huggi=
ngface.co/datasets/open-llm-leaderboard/requests</a></li>
</ul>
<p>If a model's name contains "Flagged", this indicates it has been flagged=
 by the community, and should probably be ignored! Clicking the link will r=
edirect you to the discussion about the model.</p>
<hr>
<h2>REPRODUCIBILITY</h2>
<p>To reproduce our results, here is the commands you can run, using <a hre=
f=3D"https://github.com/EleutherAI/lm-evaluation-harness/tree/b281b0921b636=
bc36ad05c0b0b0763bd6dd43463" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer">=
this version</a> of the Eleuther AI Harness:
<code>python main.py --model=3Dhf-causal-experimental --model_args=3D"pretr=
ained=3D&lt;your_model&gt;,use_accelerate=3DTrue,revision=3D&lt;your_model_=
revision&gt;"</code>
<code> --tasks=3D&lt;task_list&gt; --num_fewshot=3D&lt;n_few_shot&gt; --bat=
ch_size=3D1 --output_path=3D&lt;output_path&gt;</code></p>
